and Computer Engineering</a>, professor of Computer Science and also teaches at
Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University. Dr. Alok Choudhary is
also the founder, chairman and chief scientist of 4C insights, a data science
software company. 4C was acquired by <a href="https://www.mediaocean.com/"><span
class=SpellE>MediaOcean</span></a><span style='mso-spacerun:yes'>  </span>in
2020.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Dr.
Choudhary serves on the Secretary of Energy’s Advisory Board on Artificial
Intelligence. <b><o:p></o:p></b></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Dr. Choudhary
served as the chair of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science department
from 2007 to 2011 at Northwestern University.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> 
</span>He is a fellow of the joint Argonne-Northwestern Institute NAISE. From
1989 to 1996, Dr. Choudhary was on the faculty of the Electrical and Computer
Engineering Department at Syracuse University. </span><span style='font-size:
11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Dr. </span><span style='font-size:11.0pt;
font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Choudhary graduated with a PhD from
University of Illinois, Coordinated Science Lab, Urbana-Champaign in the field
of Supercomputing and Big Data Science. He received an M.S. degree from the
University of Massachusetts, Amherst, his B.E. (Hons.) degree from the Birla
Institute of Technology and Science, <span class=SpellE>Pilani</span>, India. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><b><span
style='mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Awards
and Recognitions: </span></b><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma'>Dr. Choudhary has received numerous prestigious awards including
National Science Foundation's Presidential Young Investigator Award, IEEE
Engineering Foundation award, an IBM Faculty award, and an Intel Research
Council award. Professor Choudhary is a fellow of the IEEE (Institute of
Electrical and Electronics Engineers), fellow of the ACM (Association of
Computing Machinery) and a fellow of the AAAS (American Academy of Advancement
of Science) - one of a select researcher, who is a fellow of top engineering,
computer science and science societies. He received the distinguished Alumni
award from Birla Institute of Technology and Science and Technology, <span
class=SpellE>Pilani</span>, India in 2016.<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> 
</span>In 2017, Dr. Choudhary was listed by <span class=SpellE>AdWeek</span> as
a “trailblazer and pioneer” in marketing technology. Prof Choudhary was also
awarded with the “Technology Manager of The Year in Chicago”, at the TIMMY
awards in 2018. In 2006 he received the first award for &quot;Excellence in
Research, Teaching and Service&quot; from the McCormick School of Engineering.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><b><span
style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;
mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Research and
Innovation:</span></b><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;
mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:
Tahoma'> Dr. Alok Choudhary has <a
href="http://cucis.ece.northwestern.edu/publications/">published</a> more than
450 <a href="http://cucis.ece.northwestern.edu/publications/">papers</a> in
various journals and international conferences and has graduated 40+ PhD
students, including 10+ women PhDs, which is one of the highest. He holds
several patents. His papers have received the best paper awards in many
conferences. He has given keynotes in almost all major international
conferences in his fields, and given more than 100 invited talks at
conferences, businesses and universities. Dr. Choudhary’s work has also
appeared in main stream media in print, digital, TV and Radio. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>His
research over the last two decades focused on big data science, supercomputing,
scalable data mining, Machine Learning/AI algorithms, software and their
applications in sciences (<span class=GramE>e.g.</span> climate understanding,
astrophysics, cosmology, designing materials etc.), medicine (<span
class=SpellE>e.g</span>, understanding diseases causes, outcome predictions,
drug design, surgeries etc.) and business applications (<span class=SpellE>e.g</span>,
business intelligence, marketing, advertising). Software and algorithms
developed by his group over the years is deployed and used in most
supercomputers in the world.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><b><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Consulting,
Advising and Leadership: </span></b><span style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:
"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>Dr. Choudhary has consulted for many
companies including Intel, SPSS, Teradata, Microsoft, Sun Microsystems, <span
class=SpellE>Newsbank</span>, Southwest Airlines, Sony, Publicis Group,
Portland Group, Lucent, Oliver <span class=SpellE>Weinmen</span>, AT&amp;T,
Netezza and many others. His research has been sponsored and supported by
DARPA, Department of Defense, NASA, Air Force, National Science Foundation,
National Institute of Health (NIH), NIST, and the Department of Energy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>He
served on a National Academy of Science, Engineering and Medicine roundtable to
develop and recommend post-secondary data science education strategies. Prof.
Choudhary served as a Member of the National Academy of Science's committee on
&quot;Impact of High-End Computing on Sciences&quot;, which was formed on
behalf of the Office of Science of the U. S. government and various federal
agencies. He has served and currently serves as board of director for multiple
companies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>He was also the co-founder
of <span class=SpellE>Accelchip</span>, a company that created software and
tools to synthesize FPGA logic configurations and circuits from high-level
languages such as MATLAB for DSP applications. <span class=SpellE>Accelchip</span>
was acquired by Xilinx in early 2006.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><span
style='font-size:11.0pt;font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:
minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:Tahoma'>A
full list of my research projects can be found in <a
href="http://cucis.eecs.northwestern.edu">CUCIS center</a>. My research group
currently consists of 2 research professors, <a
href="http://users.eecs.northwestern.edu/~wkliao">Wei-<span class=SpellE>keng</span>
Liao</a> and <a href="http://users.eecs.northwestern.edu/~ankitag">Ankit
Agrawal</a>, and many doctoral students. Their research projects and
publications can be found in <a href="http://cucis.eecs.northwestern.edu">CUCIS
center</a> website. Also, visit the CUCIS website to use various AI models and
data mining and supercomputing software developed by our group over the years.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph'><b><span
